==Finnish==

===Interrogative pronoun===
'''mikä''' (''stem'' '''mi-''')

# [[which]], [[what]].

====Declension====
The suffix ''-kä'' is retained when the case suffix doesn't add a syllable, eg. genitive singular/plural '''minkä'''. The plural forms are identical to the singular forms except in the nominative, whose plural is '''mitkä'''. The [[abessive]], [[comitative]] and [[instructive]] forms don't exist.

===Relative pronoun===
'''mikä''' (''stem'' '''mi-''')

# [[which]], [[that]].

====Declension====
The relative pronoun is declined the same way as the interrogative pronoun.

====Usage====
'''Mikä''' is used to refer to a whole sentence or a superlative.

